\ close ( stream -- ) — closing :in sends the child EOF, letting a filter
\ (tr, cat, sort, …) finish and flush. Deep test of the round-trip
\ write-in -> close :in -> read-out.

\ feed input through a command and collect its stdout
: filter ( input cmd -- output )
  run swap over write-in  dup :in @ close  read-out ;

\ upcase
"hello world" "tr a-z A-Z" filter  "HELLO WORLD" =  . cr      \ 1

\ identity (cat) preserves the bytes exactly
"a,b,c" "cat" filter  "a,b,c" =  . cr                          \ 1

\ multi-line input passes through
"ab
cd" "tr a-z A-Z" filter  "AB
CD" =  . cr                                                     \ 1

\ sort can only emit after it sees the full input + EOF
"b
a
c
" "sort" filter  "a
b
c
" =  . cr                                                      \ 1

\ empty input: close with nothing written -> empty output
"" "cat" filter  "" =  . cr                                    \ 1

\ byte count of the round-tripped output
"12345" "cat" filter size .  cr                                \ 5

\ error: close on a non-stream
5 close
